rComments: She is really not suited to teaching. This course was disorganized, she didn't seemed to know what was going on and relied heavily on blackboard while not knowing how to make it work. Lectures were repetitive and endless ramble of 3-4 ideas. The group project was a mess as well. Introduced course work in the last three days of the EXAM PERIOD. Run.

She's a bit disorganized, but a very nice person who conveys the information well. Wish the class wasn't so dependent on Blackboard or that she'd at least send notifications out when new discussion posts were added to be completed, because I wound up missing a bunch of them!

Lectures are vague unclear recounting of chapters from the textbook, read it and learn the theories yourself because they aren't taught very clearly. Midterm consisted of 3 indepth sociological questions with a 30 minute time limit in which she expected 6 examples and theories so its impossible to do well. In general, just a disorganized course.
